CL35,37 Resonance Parameter Evaluation Update, January, 2007.     1731 1451
R. O. Sayer, K. H. Guber, L. C. Leal, N. M. Larson (ORNL)         1731 1451
                                                                  1731 1451
The updated ENDF format now permits the full generality of the    1731 1451
Reich-Moore theory, including charged particle exit channels.     1731 1451
Consequently, we have updated the ENDF evaluations by adding      1731 1451
resonance parameters (RPs) to File 2, MT=151, and by including    1731 1451
the corresponding RP covariance matrices in File 32, MT=151.      1731 1451
The Reich-Moore format with LRF=3 and LCOMP=1 was                 1731 1451
utilized for CL37.  The Reich-Moore Limited (LRF=7, LCOMP=2)      1731 1451
format was used for CL35 because the proton exit channel is open  1731 1451
(Q = +0.61522 MeV).  The applicable energy range is  0.00001 eV   1731 1451
to 1.2 MeV.  Above 1.2 MeV, cross sections from the February 2000 1731 1451
ENDF evaluation are used.                                         1731 1451
                                                                  1731 1451
The Cl evaluations [1,2] were based on fits of many data sets with1731 1451
the SAMMY code [3].  In ref [2] we give detailed discussions of   1731 1451
the analysis methods used to determine parameter values and       1731 1451
uncertainties.  For capture and neutron width uncertainties, for  1731 1451
example, for each resonance several SAMMY calculations with       1731 1451
different width values were overlaid with the data.  Both the     1731 1451
overlay plots and chi-squared changes with width variation were   1731 1451
used to determine final uncertainties that were, in most cases,   1731 1451
significantly larger than the SAMMY values.  The RADCOP code [4]  1731 1451
was used to generate both File 2 and File 32.                     1731 1451
                                                                  1731 1451
At the time of the Cl evaluation, SAMMY did not incorporate the   1731 1451
now available "Prior Uncertainty Parameter", or PUP procedure.    1731 1451
Thus, some normalization and background uncertainties were not    1731 1451
propagated properly through the sequential analysis of multiple   1731 1451
data sets.  Although uncertainties in resonance energies          1731 1451
and widths are felt to be realistic, the uncertainties in         1731 1451
computed cross sections in valleys between resonances were        1731 1451
underestimated.  Furthermore, since File 32 is limited by the     1731 1451
current ENDF format to RP uncertainties and correlations,         1731 1451
uncertainties in nuclear radii cannot be treated directly.        1731 1451
These "normalization/background/radius" effects were represented  1731 1451
approximately by adjusting the File 32 uncertainties for the      1731 1451
external RPs and for selected resonances in the energy range of   1731 1451
the evaluation.                                                   1731 1451
                                                                  1731 1451
Since the resonance parameter representation does not include the 1731 1451
direct capture (DC) part of the capture cross section, the DC     1731 1451
component was included as  a "background" 1/v cross section in    1731 1451
File 3, sections 1 and 102.   At E = 0.0253 eV, the CL35 (CL37) DC1731 1451
cross section is 0.16 (0.31) b, which is a small (large) fraction 1731 1451
of the overall capture cross section of 43.60 (0.433) b.          1731 1451
The upper energy limit for the DC cross section is estimated [2]  1731 1451
to be 10 (100) keV for CL35 (CL37).   Therefore, the "background" 1731 1451
1/v cross section was terminated at these energy values.          1731 1451
