THEORY                                                            1731 1451
  HAUSER-FESHBACH STATISTICAL THEORY CALCULATIONS.  The GNASH     1731 1451
code [Yo92] was used for all Hauser-Feshbach statistical theory   1731 1451
calculations.  Preequilibrium corrections were performed in the   1731 1451
course of the GNASH calculations using the exciton model of       1731 1451
Kalbach [Ka77,Ka85].  Discrete level data from nuclear data       1731 1451
sheets were matched to continuum level densities using the        1731 1451
formulation of Gilbert and Cameron [Gi65] and pairing and shell   1731 1451
parameters from the Cook [Co67] analysis.  Neutron and charged-   1731 1451
particle transmission coefficients were obtained from the         1731 1451
optical potentials, as discussed below.  Gamma-ray transmission   1731 1451
coefficients were calculated using the Kopecky-Uhl model [Ko90].  1731 1451
  Calculations were performed for all significant reactions       1731 1451
producing neutrons, protons, deuterons, alpha particles, and      1731 1451
gamma rays for incident neutrons between 100 keV and 20 MeV.      1731 1451
  The angular distribution systematics by Kalbach [Ka88] were     1731 1451
used to describe the angular distributions for all continuum      1731 1451
particles.                                                        1731 1451
                                                                  1731 1451
  OPTICAL MODEL POTENTIALS.  For incident and exiting neutrons,   1731 1451
a phenomenological optical model potential by Arthur and Young    1731 1451
[Ar80], based on an analysis of n + Fe and p + Fe reactions, was  1731 1451
utilized for the neutron transmission coefficients, whereas the   1731 1451
potential of Watanabe [Wa94] was used to calculate the neutron    1731 1451
total cross section.  The two differenct potentials were used     1731 1451
because on the one hand the Watanabe potential agreed well with   1731 1451
total cross section measurements, whereas the Arthur potential    1731 1451
appears to give a better reaction cross section, which is very    1731 1451
important for Hauser-Feshbach calculations.  The SCAT2 optical    1731 1451
model code [Be92] was used for all calculations.                  1731 1451
   To obtain transmission coefficients for charged particle       1731 1451
reactions, the Beccetti-Greenlees potential [Be71] was used for   1731 1451
protons, the Perey and Perey [Pe63] potential for deuterons, the  1731 1451
Beccetti-Greenlees potential [Be69] for tritons,and the potential 1731 1451
of MacFadden [Mc66] was used for alpha particles.                 1731 1451
                                                                  1731 1451
  DIRECT REACTIONS:  Energy-dependent cross sections of           1731 1451
inelastic neutrons from 37Cl(n,n') direct reactions were          1731 1451
obtained using DWUCK calculations and deformation parameters      1731 1451
estimated from systematics using the compilations of Raman et     1731 1451
al. [Ra89] and Spear [Sp89].                                      1731 1451
