calculated using a combination of the GNASH and COMNUC [Du70]     1731 1451
codes for compound nucleus reactions.  Preequilibrium components  1731 1451
were included in the (n,n') reactions at higher energies to       1731 1451
approximate direct reaction effects (in an average manner) for    1731 1451
discrete states not included in the DWUCK calculations.  Cross    1731 1451
sections for a total of 30 excited states are included for 37Cl.  1731 1451
Discrete gamma-ray cross sections that exceed 1 mb are included   1731 1451
explicitly in the MF=6 distributions for all reactions.  The      1731 1451
elastic angular distributions are included in in MF =4;  the      1731 1451
(n,n') angular distributions and (n,n'gamma) multiplicities are   1731 1451
included in MF=6.                                                 1731 1451
   Cross sections (MF=3) for approximately 20 or more discrete    1731 1451
states are included for charged-particle reactions.  Again,       1731 1451
multiplicities for (n,x gamma) reactions are included in MF=6.    1731 1451
   Kalbach systematics (Ka88) are used to specify all continuum   1731 1451
particle angular distributions in MF=6.  All continuum photon     1731 1451
angular distributions are assumed isotropic.  Residual nucleus    1731 1451
recoil energy spectra are included in MF=6 for all reactions.     1731 1451
