  USE OF EXPERIMENTAL DATA.  The available experimental data for  1731 1451
37Cl is somewhat limited.  Data that were useful for the          1731 1451
evaluation are measurements of the neutron total cross section    1731 1451
for natural Cl; measurements of (n,gamma) cross sections for      1731 1451
35Cl and 37Cl at lower energies;  and a few measurements above    1731 1451
12 MeV of (n,p) and (n,alpha) cross sections.                     1731 1451
  The only adjustment made to the calculated cross sections on    1731 1451
the basis of the experimental data was to fine tune the           1731 1451
normalization of the gamma-ray strength function calculations     1731 1451
using the radiative capture measurement.  The final               1731 1451
normalization that was determined is approximately a factor of 2  1731 1451
higher than the value we have established from systematics in     1731 1451
other analyses.                                                   1731 1451
